@Ovilia ```symbolOffset``` moves symbol to one direction to make the end point visible. However if there is an end point on the other side of the symbol, it will cover the edge more. So ```symbolOffset``` is just a workaround and won't always address the issue.

I understand it will be quite complex to calculate the start/end position correctly for all types of symbols. Isn't ECharts team the A-Team to take the challenge? :-)

I'll use "circle" symbol for now and close this issue.

